<subsection xml:id="subsec-simple-intrest">
    <title>simple intrest(1)</title>

    <introduction>
        <p>
          <m>\textbf{Engage}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            In the previous section, you identified types of interest and terms related to intrest such as the 
            <m>\textbf{principal,the amount,the rate }</m> and <m>\textbf{the time}</m>.
        </p>

        <p>
            In this section, you will learn how to calculate simple intrest.
        </p>
        <definition xml:id="def-simple-intrest">
            <statement>
                <p>
                    <m>\textbf{Simple intrest(I)}</m> is the interest  calculated using only the initial principal at a given rate and time.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m>\textbf{Rate }</m> is the ratio of interest earned in a given period of time to the principle.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The rate is expressed as a percentage of the principal per annum <m>\textbf{(P.A).}</m>
                </p>
                
            </statement>
        </definition>
        <p>
            <m>\textbf{Simple Interest Formulae}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <md>
                <mrow> \text{Simple intrest }(I) =\amp \text{Principal} \times \frac{\text{Rate}}{100} \times \text{Time} </mrow>
                <mrow>I= \amp  \frac{PRT}{100}</mrow>
            </md>
        </p>
    </introduction>
  

    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-calculating-simple-interest">
        <title>Calculating simple interest in real life situations</title>
        <activity>
            <p>
                <m>{\color{green \textbf{ Work in groups}}}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                <m>\textbf{What you require:} </m> Writing materials.
            </p>
            <p>
                Ekadeli deposited <m>sh \, 20\,000 </m> a bank account for one year. The bank paid interset ate a rate of <m>7\%</m> of the deposit per annum.
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Identify the principal, the rate and the time from the information
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>\textbf{Note:}</m> Rate of <m>10\% </m> per annum means for evry <m>sh\, 100</m> principal, you earn an interest of sh 
                            <m>sh \, 10 </m> in one year.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <ol marker="(a)">
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        How much interest will <m>sh \,100</m> earn in one year at a rate of <m>7\%</m>?
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        How many hundreds are in principa of <m>sh\, 20\,000</m>?
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        How much interest will <m> sh\, 20 \,000</m> earn in one year?
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                            </ol>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Suppose Ekadeli had deposited the same <m>sh\, 20\,000</m> for two years at the same rate of <m>7\%</m> per annum. How much 
                            interest would the money earn?
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <ol marker="(a)">
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        Identify a formula that you can use to calculate the interest.
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        What do we call this type of interest?
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                            </ol>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Discuss and share your results withother groups.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </activity>
        <p>
            <m>{\color{blue} \textbf{Learning Points}}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <ul >
                <li>
                    <p>
                      The percentage at which the interest is calculated is called the 
                      <m>\textbf{rate}(R)</m>
                    </p>

                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Simple interest is the interest earned on a fixed principal over time.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        If Ekadeli had deposited <m> sh\, 15\,000</m> that earned interest at a rateb of <m>5\%</m> 
                        per yearm the simple interest at the end of two years will be:
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <m>5\%</m> means for every <m>sh\, 100 </m>, he 
                        earns  <m>sh\, 5</m> interest. Therefore, in two years :
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <m>sh\, 100 </m> earns <m>sh\, (5 \times 2)</m>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <m>sh\, 1 </m> earns <m>sh \, (\frac{5 \times 2}{100})= sh \, (\frac{5}{100} )</m>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <m>sh\, 15\, 000</m> earns <m>sh\, (\frac{5}{100} \times sh\, 15\,000 \times 2) = sh\, 1\,500</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Suppose Ekadeli  deposited <m>sh\, P</m> and interest was paid at a rate <m>R</m> 
                        for <m>T</m> years.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <m>\text{Simple interest}= \text{principal} \times \text{rate as a percentage} \times \text{time in years}</m>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <md>
                            <mrow>= \amp P \times R \times T </mrow>
                            <mrow>= \amp PRT </mrow>
                        </md>
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Franny invests Ksh <m>16\,000</m> in a savings account. She earns a simple interest rate of <m>14\%,</m> paid annually on her investment. 
                    She intends to hold the investment for <m>1\frac{1}{2}</m>years. 
                    How much simple interest did the invest earn?.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    The principal invested(P) <m>= \text{Ksh}. \, 16\,000 </m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Rate(R) <m>= 14\%</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Time(T) <m>=1\frac{1}{2}</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow> \text{Simple interest}= \amp \frac{P \times R \times T  }{100} </mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp  16\,000 \times \frac{14}{100} \times 1\frac{1}{2} </mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp 16\,000 \times \frac{14}{100} \times \frac{3}{2}  </mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp \text{Ksh.}\, 3\,360</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Simple interest earned <m>= {\color{blue} \text{Ksh.}\, 3\,360}</m>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Isadora is a maize farmer. She harvested several bags of maize and sold some of them for 
                    <m>sh.\, 850\,000</m>. She deposited the money in her account in a certain bank for nine months. 
                    The bank paid simple interest at a rate of <m>6\%</m> per annum.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="(a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                How much intersest did the money earn in the nine months?
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                What was the amount in her account at the end of the nine months?
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="(a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Principal(P) <m>= \text{Ksh} 850\,000</m>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                Rate(R) <m>= 6\%</m>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                Time(T) <m>= 9 \text{months}</m>. Express the months as a fraction of the year because the rate is per annum.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                So, time <m>=\frac{9}{12}= \frac{3}{4}</m> years.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                               <md>
                                <mrow>\text{Simple interest}= \amp \frac{P \times R \times T  }{100} \amp </mrow>
                                <mrow> =\amp 850\,000 \times \frac{6}{100} \times \frac{3}{4}</mrow>
                                <mrow> =\amp sh. 38\,250</mrow>
                               </md> 
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                The interest earned is <m>{\color{blue} sh. 38\,250}</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Amount is gotten by sum of <m>\text{principal} + \text{interest}</m>.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> \text{Amount}=\amp \text{Principal} + \text{Interest} </mrow>
                                    <mrow> =\amp sh\, 850\,000+ sh\, 38\,250</mrow>
                                    <mrow>= \amp sh\, 888\,250 </mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                The total amount in Isdora's account is <m>{\color{blue} sh\, 888\,250 }</m>.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
    </subsubsection>
    




 



    
